---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import JsonLd from '@components/seo/JsonLd.astro';
import { orgJsonLd, articleJsonLd } from '@lib/seo';

const url = 'https://strops.tools/about';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-08';
const title = 'About strops.tools';
const description = 'strops.tools is the operations cluster of a four-site host suite — free tools and printable SOPs for active short-term rental operators. Built by The STR Ledger.';
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={url} ogImage="/og/about.png">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <JsonLd data={[
      orgJsonLd(),
      articleJsonLd({
        headline: title,
        url,
        datePublished: lastUpdated,
        dateModified: lastUpdated,
      }),
    ]} />
  </Fragment>

  <article class="prose mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12">
    <div class="text-label uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-2">About</div>
    <h1>About strops.tools</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      strops.tools is the operations leg of a four-site host suite. Each site lives on
      a different stage of the host lifecycle and feeds the next one.
    </p>

    <h2>Who runs it</h2>
    <p>
      Daniel Harrison, behind <a href="https://thestrledger.com" rel="noopener">The STR Ledger</a>.
      Same shop that ships Excel templates for hosts, plus the rest of the cluster:
      strbuyers.tools (acquisition), strhost.tools (math), strops.tools (operations — you are here),
      and strguests.tools (guest XP).
    </p>

    <h2>What's free, what's not</h2>
    <p>
      Everything you can run on this site is free. The seven calculators run client-side —
      no accounts, no rate limits, no email gate on the math itself. Three printable PDFs
      are gated by email so we can keep them updated.
    </p>
    <p>
      The paid product is <a href="https://thestrledger.com" rel="noopener">The STR Ledger</a> — Excel
      workbooks for cash flow, P&amp;L, owner statements, and the rest of the financial backbone.
      Tools surface the operational gap; the Ledger turns it into reportable numbers.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      Affiliate links to operations vendors (smart locks, noise monitors, PMS, cleaner marketplaces)
      and Ledger sales. No tool here pushes you to an affiliate before it runs the math.
    </p>

    <h2>Why so plain</h2>
    <p>
      The audience is hosts who run multiple properties. Sophisticated operators tune out a hard sell
      and reward speed. Tools are the magnet; repeat use is the moat. The aesthetic is operations-utility
      on purpose.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-ink3 mt-12">
      Last updated <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{lastUpdated}</time>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
